briefdescription.para: Page item undo commands, used for collapsing undo commands.
Constructor for QgsLayoutItemPage, with the specified parent layout.
Attempts to resize the item to a specified target size.

detaileddescription.para: Note that the final size of the item may not match the specified target size, as items with a fixed or minimum size will place restrictions on the allowed item size. Data defined item size overrides will also override the specified target size.
If includesFrame is true, then the size specified by size includes the item's frame.

briefdescription.para: Creates a new layout undo command with the specified text and parent.

detaileddescription.para: The id argument can be used to specify an id number for the source event - this is used to determine whether QUndoCommand command compression can apply to the command.

simplesect.para: There is no direct setter for page orientation - use setPageSize() instead.

briefdescription.para: Returns the size of the page.
Sets the size of the page.
Sets the page size to a known page size, e.g.

detaileddescription.para:
"A4" and orientation. The known page sizes are managed by QgsPageSizeRegistry. Valid page sizes can be retrieved via QgsPageSizeRegistry::entries(). The function returns true if size was a valid page size and the page size was changed. If false is returned then size could not be matched to a known page size.
pageSize()

briefdescription.para: Returns a new page item for the specified layout.

detaileddescription.para: The caller takes responsibility for deleting the returned object.

briefdescription.para: Decodes a string representing a page orientation.

detaileddescription.para: If specified, ok will be set to true if string could be successfully interpreted as a page orientation.

briefdescription.para: Draws the item's contents using the specified item render context.

detaileddescription.para: Note that the context's painter has been scaled so that painter units are pixels. Use the QgsRenderContext methods to convert from millimeters or other units to the painter's units.

briefdescription.para: Draws the background for the item.
Draws the frame around the item.
